Fix: Tasks/Achievements claim not working after playing a game

Root cause: Tasks and Achievements screens did not refetch data when
navigating back to them after a game. React Query's staleTime:0 makes
data immediately stale but does NOT auto-refetch — a focus-based
refetch is required for mobile screens.

Changes:
- app/tasks.tsx: Added useFocusEffect + useCallback to refetch tasks
  on screen focus; added Alert when claim fails (silent failure → clear
  error message in Arabic)
- app/achievements.tsx: Same pattern — useFocusEffect refetch on focus;
  Alert on claim failure; exposed refetch from useQuery
- Both files: Added Alert and useCallback imports from React Native / React

Result: After playing a game and navigating to Tasks or Achievements,
data automatically refreshes showing updated progress. Claim button
appears correctly and shows an Arabic error alert if something goes
wrong instead of failing silently.

