Fix race condition in PlayerContext: setPlayerId after server sync

Root cause:
- `setPlayerId(id)` was called immediately after reading the player ID
  from AsyncStorage, BEFORE `GET /api/player/:id` ran on Railway.
- Tasks/Achievements queries (gated on `!!playerId`) fired the instant
  playerId was set, hitting Railway before the player profile existed.
- Railway returned 404 "player_not_found" → apiFetch returned null → []
  → screens showed empty content on fresh APK installs.

Fix (contexts/PlayerContext.tsx):
- Hoisted `let id = ""` before the outer try block so a finally clause
  can always access it.
- Removed the early `setPlayerId(id)` call (previously line 292).
- Added a `finally` block at the end of the initialization sequence that
  calls `setPlayerId(id)` after the server sync inner try/catch finishes.
- By the time `setPlayerId` fires, `GET /api/player/:id` has already run
  on Railway (creating the profile if new) so subsequent tasks/
  achievements queries are guaranteed to find the profile.
- Fallback: the `finally` block always runs even if the outer try throws
  (e.g. corrupted AsyncStorage), so the app never stays stuck with an
  empty playerId.

No changes to Railway server, multiplayer logic, or theme system.
